# XLS_URL_EXTRACTOR

> **Browser-based image downloader for editors.** Upload an Excel file with product SKUs and image URLs — download all images in one click, named by style code.

Built by **Szomer** · v1.0

---

## What it does

1. Editor uploads an `.xlsx` file containing product styles and image URLs
2. Tool reads every row and previews thumbnails
3. Editor clicks **Download All** — images save to their Downloads folder, named by **Style** (e.g. `RCP1WUY-COCMIL.jpg`)
4. Progress bar + live log shows what's downloading

No installation. No terminal. No Python. Just a browser.

---

## Live Tool

🔗 **[Open XLS_URL_EXTRACTOR](https://szomer.github.io/xls-url-extractor/)**

---

## How to use

### Option A — Use an existing Excel file
Drop any `.xlsx` that has columns for **Style** and **Image URL** into the tool.

### Option B — Start from scratch
1. Click **⬇ Download Template** inside the tool
2. Fill in your SKUs and image URLs in the downloaded Excel
3. Upload it back into the tool
4. Download all images

---

## Excel format

The tool auto-detects columns by name. These are the expected headers:

| Column | Required | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| `STYLE` | ✅ Yes | Used as the saved image filename |
| `IMAGE URL` | ✅ Yes | Direct link to the image (must start with `https://`) |
| `STYLE DESCRIPTION` | No | Human-readable product name |
| `COLOR` | No | Color name |
| `VENDOR SKU` | No | Vendor style code |
| `BC SKU` | No | Buyer / Backcountry SKU |

> **Tip:** Leave `IMAGE URL` blank for any SKU where the image isn't available yet — those rows are skipped automatically and flagged in yellow.

---

## Features

- **Drag & drop** or click to upload Excel
- **Thumbnail preview** for every image URL
- **Stats bar** — Total / Ready / Missing / Downloaded counts
- **Download All** or **Download Ready Only**
- **Individual download** button per row
- **Filter** by SKU, style, or color
- **Sort** by any column
- **Live progress log** during bulk download
- **Template generator** — download a blank pre-formatted Excel to fill in

